                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2003-06-26</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>I found this book a great source for practical tips on how to design xml documents. Get it if you have a good grasp of the theory and have used xml on occasion but don't have the experience to make great design decisions right away. All of the advice you find in this book comes from experience. It confirmed some of my own, but more often, served as an eye-opener.<BR>This statement on the back cover sums it up: "The problem here is not really a lack of information (there are many books and online resources on xml out there). The problem is a lack of reliable advice on how to use these technologies correctly and efficiently."<BR>I highly recommend it.</span>
                  
